def minor_or_major(chord):
    notes = ['C', ['C#', 'Db'], 'D', ['D#', 'Eb'], 'E', 'F', ['F#', 'Gb'], 'G', ['G#', 'Ab'], 'A', ['A#', 'Bb'], 'B']
    chord_notes = chord.split()
    flat = [note for note in notes for n in note if n in chord_notes]
    sharp = [note for note in notes for n in note if n in chord_notes]
    flat_notes = [notes.index(note) for note in flat]
    sharp_notes = [notes.index(note) for note in sharp]
    intervals_flat = [(flat_notes[i+1] - flat_notes[i]) % 12 for i in range(2)]
    intervals_sharp = [(sharp_notes[i+1] - sharp_notes[i]) % 12 for i in range(2)]
    if intervals_flat == [3, 4] or intervals_sharp == [3, 4]:
        return "Minor"
    elif intervals_flat == [4, 3] or intervals_sharp == [4, 3]:
        return "Major"
    else:
        return "Not a chord"
